To install [35;1mPenguin[0m, you must be connected to the internet!

For Wi-Fi, authenticate to the wireless network using the [32mwifi-menu[0m or [32miwctl[0m utilities.
Ethernet and Wi-Fi connections using DHCP should work automatically.

Once you have a connection, you can start the installation by running
the [32minstall.zsh[0m install script.

You can also follow the [38;2;23;147;209mArch Linux[0m installation guide:
https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Installation_guide

After connecting to the internet, the installation guide can be accessed
via the convenience script [35mInstallation_guide[0m.

